-- Hong Kong's main share index ends lower in weak volumes 
-- By Grace Li
-- Thu Jun 05, 2014 04:10AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, June 5 (Reuters) - Hong Kong's main share index was dragged lower on Thursday by heavyweights Tencent and HSBC Holdings, though H-shares rose slightly lifted by auto and insurance companies.

The Hang Seng Index <.HSI> closed down 0.2 percent at 23,109.66 points. But the China Enterprises Index <.HSCE> of the leading offshore Chinese listings in Hong Kong rose 0.5 percent. Bourse volume remained below 20-day average for a second day. Carmakers led H-share gains. Dongfeng Motor Group <0489.HK> surged 4.2 percent to close at this year's highest. BYD <1211.HK> and Great Wall Motor <2333.HK> also gained 3.5 and 1.7 percent, respectively. Tencent Holdings <0700.HK> fell 0.7 percent and HSBC Holdings Plc <0005.HK> lost 0.4 percent.